--- COMPANY DOCUMENT ---
Company Overview
Personal Home Care of New Jersey (PHCOFNJ) is an independently owned home care provider delivering professional in-home services throughout the state of New Jersey.
Name: Personal Home Care of New Jersey
Type: Licensed, insured, bonded, and accredited home care service firm
Address:	11 Deer Park Dr., Suite 102-H, Monmouth Junction, NJ 08852
Telephone:	Main: 732-230-3540  • Nurses: 732-230-3463  • Fax: 732-274-0700
Email:		info@phcofnj.com
Website:	www.phcofnj.com
Hours:		24 hours a day, 7 days a week (services available)
Industry:	Home Care / In-Home Personal & Assistive Care Services
Mission and Philosophy
Personal Home Care of New Jersey is committed to delivering professional, compassionate, and dependable home care that supports independence, safety, and dignity. Our mission is to help clients remain in their homes and communities while reducing the higher costs and emotional strain of institutional care when home-based support is appropriate.
Core Services (including but are not limited to)
Skilled nursing (through partner clinical providers and as permitted by regulation)
Personal care: bathing, hygiene, transfers, mobility support, toileting assistance, and safety supervision
Post-hospitalization support and transition assistance (non-clinical, as permitted)
Post-hospitalization rehabilitation support (non-clinical support alongside therapy plans, as permitted)
Memory care support: structured routines and safety supervision for clients with Alzheimer’s disease and other dementias
Hourly and live-in care options
Parkinson’s support (non-clinical): mobility- and safety-focused assistance and routine support
Nutrition support: meal preparation and diet-aligned assistance (non-clinical)
Companionship and communication support
Light housekeeping and laundry (care-related)
Medication reminders (non-clinical)
Appointment companionship and transportation support (as permitted)
Home safety assessments and fall-risk reduction recommendations
Respite care / family caregiver relief
Errands, shopping, and activities (arts/crafts, social participation)
Handyman-type support for home safety improvements (non-clinical, as appropriate)
Approach to Care
We use cutting-edge, AI-enabled technology to improve safety, accountability, and communication for both clients and caregivers. This includes secure mobile tools for caregivers, real-time communication, and remote patient monitoring through connected devices and smart health gadgets that provide timely updates, alerts, and trend insights—helping our team respond earlier when risks arise.
We use our Hospital-at-Home module to enable doctors to meet with patients through secure video visits, assess symptoms, make clinical decisions, and guide treatment remotely—while coordinating in-home services and follow-up as needed.
Our technology is designed to connect key branches of care and funding—caregivers, families, providers, and payers, and where applicable state/Medicaid programs and managed care organizations—so everyone operates from the same plan of care. This connected homecare ecosystem strengthens coordination across referrals, transitions of care, and ongoing service delivery in the home and community.
We also use EVV (Electronic Visit Verification) to confirm visit start/end times and location, strengthen compliance, and ensure transparent service delivery. Care plans, caregiver notes, incidents, and quality indicators are captured digitally and aggregated into dashboards and standardized reports for oversight and quality improvement. AI-driven analytics can flag exceptions (missed visits, unusual patterns, rising fall risk, or changes in condition) to support proactive intervention.
The agency’s approach is client-centered and culturally sensitive. We provide multilingual support when needed so that communication and cultural preferences are respected.
PHCOFNJ focuses on individualized care planning, working collaboratively with the client and family to deliver services aligned with personal preferences and care goals.
We emphasize empathy and professionalism - clients are treated with dignity and respect and are never “just a case number.”
The agency assists in assessing and updating a home for safety by identifying and recommending modifications that reduce fall risk and other hazards.
Professional Team
The care team consists of certified and highly trained professionals experienced in delivering non-medical support services, and—where applicable—coordinating with clinical partners for medical services.
Corporate Affiliations
Personal Home Care of New Jersey maintains partnerships with:
Personal Home Care of North Carolina
Personal Home Care of Maryland
Target Clients
The agency serves a broad range of individuals and families, including:
Adults recovering from medical events, surgery, or hospitalization (discharge-to-home support)
Seniors needing daily life support, safety supervision, and help with activities of daily living
Individuals with chronic conditions who benefit from ongoing assistance, monitoring, and care coordination
Individuals with cognitive impairment (Alzheimer’s/dementia) who need structure, routine, and safety support
Clients with mobility limitations, fall risk, or post-rehab needs (safe transfers and home-safety support)
Individuals with disabilities who need assistance to live independently at home
Family caregivers seeking respite support, relief coverage, and coordination of services
Clients requiring long-term in-home assistance to maintain independence and quality of life
Hospice/palliative-support clients and families needing non-medical supportive care in coordination with clinical providers
Medicaid/LTC insurance beneficiaries who require authorized services and compliant documentation
Pediatric clients and families who need in-home support and caregiver relief (as appropriate and within scope of services)
Reputation & Reviews
Public review listings indicate that PHCOFNJ is an established local provider with a positive community presence. While detailed user ratings may be limited on major platforms, the agency can provide references, testimonials, and performance reporting upon request.
